    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom of the stems are turning this sickly yellow color but the top ones look okay. what's probably going on and how do i fix the soil?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing leaves on the bottom of your tomato plants, while the top ones are fine, often suggests a nutrient issue, most likely a sign of nitrogen deficiency. You can try to fix this by applying a balanced, slow-release fertilizer, or by feeding them a liquid fertilizer rich in nitrogen. If you suspect the soil itself is the problem, you might want to amend it with aged compost to improve its overall health and nutrient retention. Remember, a good, rich soil is the foundation for a healthy tomato harvest!",
      "source": "target",
